 Justus Howell was gunned down from behind by an officer in Zion , Illinois after officers were called to reports of an argument .
The chief of the Zion Police Department has said that the argument was in fact a scuffle over a handgun - during which the firearm went off and Howell allegedly pointed it at another teenager .
Police say Howell had just taken a weapon from Tramond Peet , 18 , who was trying to sell it to him .
